author: Kelly Mclaughlin For Mailonline
title: Frontier plane clips Southwest aircraft's wing at Phoenix | Daily Mail Online
text: Near-miss at Phoenix airport as a Frontier plane clips the wing of Southwest aircraft at the departure gate A Frontier Airlines plane clipped a Southwest plane at Sky Harbor Airport The plane was pushing away from its gate at Terminal 3 at around 8pm when it hit the aircraft, which was taxiing nearby No injuries were reported in the incident, but the collision caused a fuel leak National Transportation Safety Board and FAA were performing an investigation as of Thursday night Published: 12:39 GMT, 17 February 2017 | Updated: 14:14 GMT, 17 February 2017 60 shares
